editorialSummary.text: Fried, broiled & steamed seafood served from a cozy, unassuming counter-serve spot.

originalText.text: I finished the food so fast because it was soooo good i wish i took more photos besides of the plantains. I got scallops that was broiled to perfection making it taste like crab and i got friend shrimp. It was amazing.

originalText.text: I had the fish dinner  with green beans and a salad. The fried fish fillets were cooked perfect and also the fresh green beans grilled with garlic were excellent and also the salad. I am impressed with this , because I ordered this through door dash and I am 2 and a half miles away and it was still warm and the fillets were crunchy .The fillets were laid out on top of green beans  in a manner that kept the fillets crunchy. Great to know I can order a Great fish dinner when I’m working!

originalText.text: I try to stop by here whenever I'm in the neighborhood.  The fish, calamari and chips combo, salmon steaks and red snapper are my favorites, although everything on the menu is worth trying; the sides by themselves are delicious.  This is also one of the few places where the jumbo shrimp actually live up to their name; they're sizable, juicy and delicious.  The friendly, (authentic) Harlem vibe and flavor combined with the old-school chip shop feel make it a great experience, and the staff know the regulars.  Highly recommended all around.

originalText.text: I am writing this in hope that the owner of this establishment can see this. Today I ordered food for my Husband. The food was paid for online and I received the text that my food was ready! I go in and there was an elderly lady who was working there very short in stature. I showed her the text message about my order and she refused to give me my food stating that so many people come in there and take food that is not theirs!!! This is no way to treat a paying customer. My family, friends and I have slent so much money with this estabkishment over the years!!!  The flaws in your syatem have nothing to do with me! I do not steal food nor does my family.   I cursed her out because I also over heard her saying to a co- worker that I better never come there while she is working there and I took that as a threat!!! I do not care how old she said she is, she needs to learn how to treat paying customers!! Furthermore,  an hour after this I was already home because I do not live in that area anymore and received another text that my food was ready even though I had already picked it up. Please fix the system and train your staff so no one has to go through this again!!!
